HEADWORD: Anthrenus
<hw>An*thre"nus</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n*thr⟦emac⟧"n⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>'anqrh`nh</grk> a hornet.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of small beetles, several of which, in
the larval state, are very destructive to woolen goods, fur, etc. The
common ⟦ldquo⟧museum pest⟦rdquo⟧ is <spn>Anthrenus varius</spn>; the
carpet beetle is <spn>Anthrenus scrophulari⟦ae⟧</spn>. The larv⟦ae⟧ are
commonly confounded with moths.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

